In our childhood when we used to see our uncles doing labor, we used to pray to Allah: Please save us from this hard labor.
To avoid this we wrote a letter to the editor of the daily Amroz and asked him what we should do after matriculation so that we don't have to do labor.
The editor wrote in reply that we should select certain subjects and become doctors or engineers.
